gomodel:SYNGO_369  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Gephyrin is essential for the postsynaptic localization of glycine receptors (GlyR). Antisense knock-down of Gephyrin expression suppresses clustering of GlyR.\n\n29/3/2017 Pim\n- The experiment shows GlyR clusters at the membrane as opposed to intracellular GlyR hotspots. The membrane GlyR clusters are inferred to reflect GlycR clusters in the postsynaptic membrane.\n- The GlyR hotspots are presumed to be synaptic receptors by the authors and a er opposed to GPHN which is a marker for a postsynaptic specialization (see feedback thread).. Experimental description: ... sections of primary neurons from embryonic rat spinal cord... p. 746" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_369" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

